last_episode_to_air.name: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.

name: Mighty Magiswords
overview: Prohyas and Vambre, the brother and sister team of Warriors for Hire, are always up for a quest. But they never know what quest will drop in their laps! Giant pigs, giant spiders, or giant ancient dinosaurs, they can handle whatever giant quest you want; but not without their trusted collection of Magiswords.

episodes.name: Mushroom Menace
episodes.overview: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

episodes.name: The Mystery of Loch Mess
episodes.overview: Prohyas and Vambre must save captured innocents from Queen Porcina.

episodes.name: Squirrelled Domination
episodes.overview: The Warriors are hired to gather some golden acorns, but Vambre remembers she has a fear of squirrels and tries to avoid it.

episodes.name: Case Clothed
episodes.overview: Princess Zange hires the Warriors to be her secret service while she goes shopping.

episodes.name: Surely You Jesto
episodes.overview: The Warriors think that housesitting for Omnibus is boring work.

episodes.name: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
episodes.overview: The Warriors notice Grup has an obnoxious odor and tries to clean him, but Grup tries to avoid them, being afraid of water.

episodes.name: Flirty Phantom
episodes.overview: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas.

episodes.name: The Wrath of Neddy
episodes.overview: The Cave Weirdos are displaced from their cave by Neddy the Mallet and turn to the Warriors to help them reclaim their place.

episodes.name: Working for Scales
episodes.overview: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

episodes.name: Felonious Prose
episodes.overview: The Warriors search for a contact lens is compromised by Vambre's obsession with a Veronica Victorious novel.

episodes.name: Potion in the Ocean
episodes.overview: Witchy Simone joins the Warriors on a mission deep in the Fickle Sea to find an eye of newt for her magic potion, but Man Fish the Fish Man won't let them harm his sea newt pal!

episodes.name: Bad Bad Cop
episodes.overview: Vambre and Prohyas pretend to be cops in their attempts to shakedown a dangerous bunch of pirates to find a broccoli smuggler.

episodes.name: Gotta Get Grup to Get Down
episodes.overview: Grup hires the Warriors to help him become the biggest music star in Rhyboflaven, yet helping the little dragon achieve his big dream is no small task.

episodes.name: Thick as Thieves
episodes.overview: Phil the Pilferer robs Vambre and Prohyas of their very best Magiswords so he can snag the Sheepy Mantis, but the Warriors find out that no Magisword is lame as they manage to keep Phil from becoming Thief of the Year.

episodes.name: Biggest Fan
episodes.overview: An obsessed super fan goes to dangerous extremes just to be saved by her Warrior heroes: Vambre and Prohyas.

episodes.name: Dungeons and Dayjobs
episodes.overview: A botched mission leaves the Warriors in debt, so they take day jobs at Slugburger and sling Slugburgers for Witchy Simone!

episodes.name: Little Sword of Horrors
episodes.overview: Prohyas grows a new Magisword from a tiny seed, but doesn't know that his Carnivorous Plant Magisword is a menace to Lyvsherian society until its too late!

episodes.name: Champions of Breakfast
episodes.overview: An epic battle between Vambre and her Waffle Magisword and Prohyas' Pancake Magisword escalates to a war that can only end when Grup solicits his Cave Weirdo pals to be peacemakers.

episodes.name: Gut Feelings
episodes.overview: With help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword, the Warriors help get to the root of who stole all the vegetable Magiswords that belong to the angry bunny, Hoppus.

episodes.name: The Tome of Morrow
episodes.overview: Noville's Magisword training with Vambre pays off and the Warriors invite him on a mission to an ancient cave in the Barren Faceland to find the rare and sacred book, the Tome of Morrow.

episodes.name: Share and Share Dislike
episodes.overview: Super Shooting Star Magisword is the coolest Magisword ever, but Vambre and Prohyas can't seem to share it, and even a quest to reclaim the never-melting ice cube back from Frosteratu can't shake their obsession.

episodes.name: Grup Jam
episodes.overview: Grup invents the "new" sport of basketball, but the stakes are too high for the Warriors to let him play the Galacton team, as the winner shall rule the Kingdom of Rhyboflaven.

episodes.name: Bad Man Oldman
episodes.overview: When the Warriors re-thatch Old Man Oldman's roof and absentmindedly make it look like Prohyas' hair, Oldman dons an giant evil toupee exacts his revenge!

episodes.name: Witchy Simone Ruins Everything
episodes.overview: Witchy Simone joins Witch Way, but Gateaux is the odd cat out so he hires the Warriors to break up Witchy Simone and Morbidia and defeat a mission that has King Rexxtopher hopping mad!

episodes.name: Strange Nedfellows
episodes.overview: Omnibus hires the Warriors to get a one-of-a-kind salmon for his fancy aquarium, but Neddy joins them on their quest and wants the "Queen Sal," yet Man Fish the Fish Man wants the salmon to stay in the Fickle Sea!

episodes.name: Action Comedy
episodes.overview: Rhyboflaven's local fictional superhero, Broccoli Punch, has an all-new, spectacular action stage show, but when Flonk masquerades as the star, the Warriors disguise themselves as broccoli bad guys to teach the imposter a lesson!

episodes.name: Random Acts of Memory
episodes.overview: The Warriors learn that Nohyas has been using a Selective Memory Magisword to erase select interactions with Prohyas' bizarre doppelganger their entire lives, so their new mission: take back that sword!

episodes.name: Elect to Decline
episodes.overview: Noville wants to impress Vambre with a new Magisword from the Cave of Stuff, but the Cave Weirdos are in election mode and horrible smear campaigning is making Noville's simple task impossible!

episodes.name: They See Me Trollblin
episodes.overview: The tiny Kotassians hire the Warriors to exterminate two humongous Trollblins that have invaded their village.

episodes.name: Hideous Hound
episodes.overview: Prohyas pets an unsightly stray dog, and from that moment on the poor pooch appears on a variety of Warrior missions, driving Vambre and Vambre's brain insane!

episodes.name: Getting Ahead
episodes.overview: When the headless body of Omnibus knocks at their door, the Warriors use Magiswords to try to make a head they can talk to with mixed results!

episodes.name: The Cave of Gelatinous Doom!
episodes.overview: The Warriors don't have a worthy adventure to use their impressive new skull-and-crossbones-emblazoned Bonehead Magisword until they are sent on a quest to battle a mighty slime beast in the Dungeon of Gelatinous Doom!

episodes.name: Pachydermus Interruptus
episodes.overview: A battle with Man Fish the Fish Man leaves Warriors For Hire HQ in shambles, so landlord, Mr. Pachydermus, has the Warriors repair the damage-- but without Magiswords!

episodes.name: Squideo Games
episodes.overview: When Vambre and Prohyas are hired for separate gigs, they end up having to battle each other to claim a rare Squideo from Lake Sprite in Galacton.

episodes.name: Sibling Sorcery
episodes.overview: When Phil the Pilferer steals the Golden Broomstick Magisword Award intended for Witchy Simone's famous younger sister, Witchy Sparkles, the Warriors lead the search in getting it back.

episodes.name: Don't Read the Comments
episodes.overview: An obsession with comments and criticisms about him on the Board of Opinions drives Prohyas nuts.

episodes.name: Hoppus the Hunted
episodes.overview: The bunny sorceress, Danelda, has been on the search for Hoppus so she can take him back to their rabbit village, but Hoppus is too enamored by Kablammica and her broccoli soup to ever go back!

episodes.name: Transylbabies
episodes.overview: A mission to babysit Snowmanpire babies in Transylbiria leads Vambre and Prohyas to attack the local monster townsfolk in misguided attempts to keep the Snowbabies safe.

episodes.name: Bureaucrophobia
episodes.overview: Teri Gargantuan is in trouble and her spider kids hire the Warriors to save their mom from a mad mercenary spider hunter.

episodes.name: Continue?
episodes.overview: The Mysterious Hooded Woman hires the Warriors to retrieve the Orb of Sphericity from a temple in Galacton. The odd thing is, this temple has save points! When the Warriors are defeated, they respawn, but Vambre remembers what happened and Prohyas does not.

episodes.name: Hunting for Scavengers
episodes.overview: When an impish weather gnome sends the Warriors and friends on a competitive quest, the drive to win threatens the group's fight against a conjured monster.

episodes.name: Get That BORFL!
episodes.overview: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven.

episodes.name: Unconventional Dolphinism
episodes.overview: Since Prohyas is taking Dolphin Magisword to the Dolphin Convention, Vambre asks Witchy Simone to join her on a search for the Narwhal Magisword, angering a deadly Sealdebeast guard that lures dolphins away from the convention in the process.

episodes.name: Letter Wronging Campaign
episodes.overview: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

episodes.name: The Saga of Robopiggeh!
episodes.overview: A botched rescue attempt damages their robot pal, RoboPiggeh, and Vambre and Prohyas must battle the evil cyborg, Tera-Bite, in Galacton, who is determined to dismantle their broken pal for being obsolete.

episodes.name: Bad Heir Day
episodes.overview: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

episodes.name: Docky & Buford's Decidedly Pathetic Adventure
episodes.overview: Docky Boardman and Buford want to beef up business for the Rhyboflaven Boardwalk, but in their hunt for a new attraction, they get eaten by a mammoth-sized Ramblyboo and it's up to the Warriors to get them out!

episodes.name: School's In, Oh Bummer!
episodes.overview: It turns out that Vambre and Prohyas didn't graduate the Adventure Academy after all and need to go back to school earn their diplomas!

episodes.name: Taming of the Swords
episodes.overview: The Warriors attempt to tame two of their most problematic Magiswords, Taunting Jester and Carnivorous Plant, with the help of their expert Magiswordsmith mother, Kablammica.

episodes.name: Quest for Knowledge!
episodes.overview: After a flashback where we learn the origins of the Warriors passion for Magiswords, they return to Adventure Academy where Professor Cyrus sets V and P and their former classmates on a quest to find the Legendary Knowledge Magisword.

episodes.name: Collection Infection
episodes.overview: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

episodes.name: To Balderly Go
episodes.overview: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

episodes.name: For the Love of Narwhal
episodes.overview: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

episodes.name: Winning at Whining
episodes.overview: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

episodes.name: Suitable Armor
episodes.overview: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

episodes.name: Changeable Terraingable
episodes.overview: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

episodes.name: Fixing-a-Flonk!
episodes.overview: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

episodes.name: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohayas Warrior
episodes.overview: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

episodes.name: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
episodes.overview: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

episodes.name: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
episodes.overview: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

episodes.name: The Status of Cattus
episodes.overview: The Warriors want someone to enjoy collecting Magiswords as much as they do, so they go crazy trying to interest Cattus the Oneblade into obtaining more.

episodes.name: Goat!
episodes.overview: Prohyas becomes obsessed with riding an uncooperative goat to get over a mountain.

episodes.name: Team of Broccoli
episodes.overview: The Warrior Family's broccoli crop is stolen and the Warriors and Danelda team up to track it down underground.

episodes.name: Mall of Shame
episodes.overview: Vambre gets locked inside Mount Ma'all so Prohyas tries to get her out while Vambre does her best to escape from the inside.

episodes.name: Agent of Destruction
episodes.overview: DeBizz helps the Warriors become more famous as their agent, but Vambre returns to adventuring while Prohyas gets caught up in the DeBizz fame trap.

episodes.name: Straining Day
episodes.overview: The Warriors teach Witchy Simone and her Slugburger crew how to use Magiswords. Prohyas teaches the basics while impatient Vambre tries to teach "the good stuff" too fast.

episodes.name: Dunkadelic
episodes.overview: After suffering trauma from being the dunk-ee in a dunking booth, Prohyas has trouble getting through the dunk based traps in Man Fish's lair.

episodes.name: The Incredible Tiny Warriors
episodes.overview: The Warriors must use a Legendary Magisword to defeat a giant king who wants to eat celebrities. This proves difficult when being eaten by the King makes Vambre feel very small.

episodes.name: Helping Cattus Help
episodes.overview: The search for a mythical creature gets rather metaphysical when the equally elusive Cattus' assists the mission.

episodes.name: Warts and All
episodes.overview: Witchy Simone accidentally turns Vambre into a frog and Prohyas and Witchy try to change her back.

episodes.name: Too Commercial
episodes.overview: The Warriors go advertising crazy; Grup tries to stop them for their own good!

episodes.name: Like Water for Bimm
episodes.overview: Vambre helps to get Bimm over her mission crippling fear of water.

episodes.name: The Pecking Order
episodes.overview: Professor Cyrus hires the Warriors to take Frank-Paul through a treacherous mountain pass so he can molt at the top of Mt. Chickicken.

episodes.name: Manlier Fish the Fishlier Man
episodes.overview: With the help of a conch shell genie, Man Fish upgrades himself in various ways to defeat the Warriors.

episodes.name: The Lanolion Sleeps Tonight
episodes.overview: Bimm and Familiar shadow the Warriors on a mission in the Sheepy Jungle, but put under such close scrutiny, the Warriors find that they're unable to be themselves!

episodes.name: The Ballad of Sailor Sidney
episodes.overview: The Warriors go on a mission to find missing Sailor Sidney for the Keelhaul Cove Pirates.

episodes.name: Extreme Dreams
episodes.overview: Phibby Croax hires the Warriors for the MOST EXTREME EXPERIENCE EVER!

episodes.name: Forever a Fishstick
episodes.overview: After a misfire with Fishstick Magisword, Prohyas copes with completing Warrior missions as a fish stick.

episodes.name: Sorry for Party OCHing
episodes.overview: The Warriors struggle to keep poise at Princess Zange's exclusive party, but all bets are off when a feud with Witch Way escalates into a Magic vs. Magiswords war!

episodes.name: A Mind Is a Terrible Thing
episodes.overview: The Warriors easily thwart Phil's latest plan with Legendary Knowledge Magisword so Phil repeatedly tries to steal it from them.

episodes.name: Bewitched, Bothered and Bothered Some More!
episodes.overview: Flonk hires the Warriors to make Witch Way change his brother Helmut from a frog back to human.

episodes.name: Train on a Snake
episodes.overview: Lady Hiss hires the Warriors to train her to be super tough.

episodes.name: King of the Zombeez
episodes.overview: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

episodes.name: Hiccup the Volume
episodes.overview: Monkey Chunks has hiccups and Biblia Tick hires the Warriors to get rid of them.

episodes.name: Ghosthaste
episodes.overview: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

episodes.name: Hangry Hangry Hoppus
episodes.overview: The Warriors battle a monster version of Hoppus, the rabbit transformed by the Cursed Garlic Magisword.

episodes.name: Pachydermus Packard and the Camp of Fantasy
episodes.overview: A doctor orders Mr. Pachydermus to have an adventure, so he attends the Warriors' super-annoying Fantasy Camp.

episodes.name: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
episodes.overview: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.
